PSGRAPH version 0.04
====================

PSGRAPH is a module that can convert data in delimited ASCII format into graphs either in batch or individual mode. It has been tested under Ubuntu and CentOS but should work under any system that supports perl. 

As of this version, supported graphs are 2d pies, column and bar charts. Others are under development. The module calculates the graphs in Postscript, which allows for unlimited scaling. Exports include all formats supported by imagemagick.

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

ImageMagick (http://www.imagemagick.org/script/index.php)

